  "prompt": "Is leave letter necessary for tourist visa?",
  "response": "The necessity of a leave letter depends on the specific visa requirements of the country you're applying to and your personal circumstances. However, in many cases for tourist visas:\n\n1. Employment letter/leave approval:\n- If you're employed, some countries may require:\n- A letter from your employer confirming your employment\n- Approved leave/vacation period\n- Proof of return to work after the trip\n\n2. General requirements might include:\n- Proof of financial stability\n- Travel itinerary\n- Accommodation details\n- Return ticket\n- Travel insurance\n\n3. Variations by country:\n- Visa requirements differ for each country\n- Some are strict, others more lenient\n- Check specific embassy guidelines\n\n4. Recommended steps:\n- Consult the embassy website\n- Contact visa processing center\n- Verify exact documentation needed\n- Prepare documents in advance\n\n5. Employment status matters:\n- Employed: Often need leave letter\n- Self-employed: Different documentation\n- Student: May need academic leave proof\n- Retired: Different requirements\n\n6. Best practice:\n- Always check current visa requirements\n- Prepare comprehensive documentation\n- Start visa application process early\n\nRecommendation: Verify specific requirements with the destination country's embassy or consulate.",
